The Yearbook Staff is hard at work trying to complete their pages: with that being said the school closure is causing us to be creative with what to fill those pages with that were slated to hold pictures of Track, Prom, Honor's Night etc...
Here's where you come in! We would like you to submit pictures of you and your family (especially your siblings that are also enrolled at LCC) at home during this time. Here are some suggestions that we brainstormed this week: pictures of you baking, working out, cleaning, playing board games, working on homework, farming, organizing your room, Sunday Cruise Day, Scavenger Road Rally, etc... PreK- 12th grade are encouraged to submit pictures.
You can submit picture in two ways: email them to jennifer.kesting@lccschool.org or download the yearbook app "Replay It" and submit them directly to the yearbook website!

Due to the current COVID-19 health situation, there will be restricted access to LCC School district facilities effective Tuesday, March 17th.

The LCC Fitness Centers and Gyms, both in Laurel and Coleridge, are closed to public access until further notice.

Additionally, the LCC Learning Center Library is closed to public access until further notice.

There will be no outside activities permitted at school facilities while the current school closure is in effect.

Throughout the school closure, the LCC district office will remain open for business, with staff prepared to address patron questions.

We truly understand any frustration caused by these announced closures. We remain hopeful to return to normal operations in the coming weeks.
